                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17681207-2-off7 t17681207-2-crimeloc9"></join>. I went to Horn-fair, at Charlton, on the 18th of Oct. and lock'd my room door, about nine in the forenoon: the two prisoners are my lodgers in a garret; I have two rooms in the same house: when I came home, about eight at night, I miss every thing I had, ( mentioning the things laid in the indictment) which I had left safe in my room. Berrisfort was gone away, Flint was in the house. I told her I had been robbed. She said she was very sorry, and told me Berrisfort had done it, and had pawned the things.</p>
               <p>Q. Where was your husband?</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="176812070004"></xptr>
            
